REPLICATION
Master: 192.168.1.10 Read and Write
Replica: 192.168.1.20 Read Only

On Master edit config
/etc/mysql/my.cnf

[mysqld]
server-id=1
log_bin=mysql-bin

And restart mysql

Now create replica user on Master
CREATE USER 'replica'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY ‘pass@123’;
GRANT REPLICATION SLAVE ON . TO 'replica'@'%';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

In mysql run this 
SHOW MASTER STATUS; //to get log position to put in connection query

Now export database 
mysqldump -u root -p --all-databases --master-data > dump.sql

Import it on replication database 
mysql -u root -p < dump.sql

On Slave  edit config
/etc/mysql/my.cnf

server-id=2

Restart mysql

On Replica server in my sql connect master 

CHANGE MASTER TO
MASTER_HOST='192.168.1.10',
MASTER_USER='replica',
MASTER_PASSWORD='pass@123',
MASTER_LOG_FILE='mysql-bin.000001',
MASTER_LOG_POS=157;

And run this to start slave copying data from master
START SLAVE;

SHOW SLAVE STATUS\G; // to check status
Slave_IO_Running: Yes
Slave_SQL_Running: Yes
